main event: A ground radar observation reported a single unidentified object moving slightly over the center of Baltimore on May 21.
interesting points: The observation noted that the object was still for a while before moving slightly., The officer believed the object to be a reflection from city lights., The concluded possibilities for the object included a balloon, meteor, or possibly an identified aircraft., The observation duration was unknown., Only one object was observed during this incident.
witness description: a civilian age 33, land lithographer operator
